cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.DL, cs.DB, cs.SI 

The paper discusses the integration of Web directories with the Semantic Web vision, which involves the use of ontologies to describe the semantics of Web resources and categories. This suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories, as well as deep learning (cs.DL) and database (cs.DB) sub-categories, which are all relevant to the use of ontologies in organizing and managing web content. Additionally, the paper discusses the evaluation of Web directory structure quality, which could fall under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI) as it involves assessing the usability and effectiveness of a network structure.
